final_words: "To Bert Michelbacher, I am sorry for the part I played in your wife's death. For Haddon and Baldwin, I can't help you. You still have to keep looking. I'm sorry for your family. I can't help you. I took part in the Michelbacher murder, I can't help you guys. I'm sorry." Rhodes then told his mom "goodbye." He then turned to the executioner or the warden and uttered, "I forgive you, I really do."
